subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus.
(
Figs. 7–9
). Phallus is long, thin, slightly flattened in dorso-ventral direction in its basal half, much more flattened in the apical half and flat at the apex (
Figs. 8–9
). Its width is almost uniform from the base to the apical part, where it narrows to the sharp point. Tegmen with short paramerae, which carry long setae (
Fig. 7
). Accessory glands in the reproductive system of the male are absent.
